# AXIONAX FRONTEND — Web Universe (Git Submodule)

The frontend project lives at **web-universe/** (Git submodule pointing to `axionax-web-universe` repo).  
Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, pnpm workspaces, TurboRepo

## Structure (inside `web-universe/`)

```
axionax-web-universe/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/           ← Next.js 14 App Router — main portal, explorer, staking UI
│   └── marketplace/   ← Vite + React — compute job marketplace
└── packages/
    ├── sdk/           ← @axionax/sdk — RPC calls, wallet, ABI, types, contract wrappers
    └── ui/            ← @axionax/ui — shared design system (Tailwind + Radix-based)
```

## Rules

### Always
- Use **pnpm** — never `npm` or `yarn` at the web-universe root
- Use workspace aliases: `import { ... } from "@axionax/sdk"` — never relative cross-package paths
- Default to **Server Components** in Next.js; add `"use client"` only for hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, wallet events)
- **All blockchain logic** (RPC, ABI, contract calls, wallet) goes in `packages/sdk` — apps only consume it
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env vars for client-side config only

### Never
- Never put reusable business logic in `apps/web` or `apps/marketplace` — move to `packages/sdk`
- Never hardcode API keys, private keys, or RPC credentials in frontend code
- Never use `npm install` or `yarn add` — always `pnpm --filter <pkg> add <dep>`
- Never import types from `apps/` into `packages/` (one-way dependency)

